Text.SourceString: You must be <PlayerName>$player</>, right?//<portrait=normal>Damn, I wasn’t expecting you to look like THIS.//You’re surprisingly cute!

Well, it’s nice to finally meet you! Name’s <NPCName>Pablo</>.//I don’t know jack about farming, but hey!//<portrait=happy>If you need help with tools, come by my shop just north of town, and I’ll see what I can do. Ciao!
It’s important to have a hobby.//Gives you an opportunity to know yourself better, if you think about it.
Little things, like what we do for fun…//That’s what makes us who we are, eh?
I try to see my friends after work, most days.//You know, just to unwind.
But if I’m too tired, I’ll just chill in the garage and tinker with my speakers.//<portrait=happy>No big deal.
I try to see my friends after work, most days.//You know, just to unwind.
But if I’m too tired, I’ll just chill in the garage and tinker with my speakers.//<portrait=happy>No big deal.
We develop a new weapon every now and then…//Well, basically whenever we have the time, to be honest with you.
Don’t worry about our weapons breaking in the middle of combat.//They’re well made!
We develop a new weapon every now and then…//Well, basically whenever we have the time, to be honest with you.
Just make sure to check out our shop often, if you’re interested!
I usually take two days to upgrade tools, so please plan accordingly if you want yours worked on.
No… I still can’t expedite it, no matter how much more you pay.

No… I still can’t expedite it, no matter how much more you pay.
We develop a new weapon every now and then…//Well, basically whenever we have the time, to be honest with you.
Just make sure to check out our shop often, if you’re interested!
Hmm?//<portrait=normal>Oh! Yes, we make weapons and armor for monster slaying.//And we sell them, of course.
Don’t worry about our weapons breaking in the middle of combat.//They’re well made!
We develop a new weapon every now and then…//Well, basically whenever we have the time, to be honest with you.
Just make sure to check out our shop often, if you’re interested!
It’s important to have a hobby.//Gives you an opportunity to know yourself better, if you think about it.
Little things, like what we do for fun…//That’s what makes us who we are, eh?
<NPCName>Ben</>'s the man if you want a fresh perspective.//I like to get his opinion when I’ve got a tough decision to make.
He has a different outlook than most… Cool dude.
Did you know that <NPCName>Frank</> hates yogurt?//<portrait=normal>A weird thing to hate, isn’t it?
He also hates durian, but that one I understand.//<portrait=concerned>I’m not a fan of durian, myself.
Business hours? You sound so formal, <PlayerName>$player</>. Ha ha.//Our shop is open Monday to Saturday. We’re closed on Sunday.
<NPCName>Rafael</> wants a day off to spend time with the rest of the family, so we decided to close the shop on Sundays.//He’s usually gone all day.//<portrait=normal>It gives me time to relax.
We close early on Saturdays.//<portrait=normal>So if you need my help, better ask before noon.
My free time? Hmm…//I usually head to town and run some errands…//If not that, I’ll probably just hang out at the Tavern.
Having a good day so far?
My brother and I always share the workload, even when there’s not a lot to do.//It keeps things fair, I think.
<NPCName>Ben</>’s the man if you want a fresh perspective.//I like to get his opinion when I’ve got a tough decision to make.
He has a different outlook than most… Cool dude.
We close early on Saturdays.//<portrait=normal>So if you need my help, better ask before noon.
My free time? Hmm…//I usually head to town and run some errands…//If not that, I’ll probably just hang out at the Tavern.
My cousin <NPCName>Antonio</>, <NPCName>Valentina</>’s dad, comes here for festivals sometimes.
<NPCName>Valentina</>… Errr… <NPCName>Suki</>’s daughter.//Ring a bell?
Did you know that <NPCName>Frank</> hates yogurt?//<portrait=normal>A weird thing to hate, isn’t it?
He also hates durian, but that one I understand.//<portrait=concerned>I’m not a fan of durian, myself.
My cousin <NPCName>Antonio</>, <NPCName>Valentina</>’s dad, comes here for festivals sometimes.
<NPCName>Valentina</>… Errr… <NPCName>Suki</>’s daughter.//Ring a bell?
You look like you had a good day!
Any plans for the weekend?
My brother and I always share the workload, even when there’s not too much to do.//<portrait=normal>It keeps things fair, I think.
<NPCName>Ben</>’s the man if you want a fresh perspective.//I like to get his opinion when I’ve got a tough decision to make.
He has a different outlook than most… Cool dude.
I dropped some eggs today when I was trying to make breakfast. Such a waste of food.
When it comes to birthdays, I think people are just happy if you remember. It shows they’re on your mind.
Of course, gifts never hurt either!
I go to the Tavern often. Ha ha. You noticed, huh?//<portrait=normal>Sometimes after work, and on the weekend. Just whenever I feel like it.
The food is good, and the vibe is lively… What more do I want, right?
Your tools holding up all right, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Bring them over if you need anything fixed, will ya? I’ll see what I can do.
I dropped some eggs today when I was trying to make breakfast. Such a waste of food.
I keep forgetting to read this book my brother got me about legendary blacksmiths.
Maybe tonight I’ll actually pick it up and read the darn thing?
I keep forgetting to read this book my brother got me about legendary blacksmiths.
Maybe tonight I’ll actually pick it up and read the darn thing?
Are your tools holding up all right?
Bring them over if you need anything fixed, will ya? I’ll see what I can do.
It’s <Italic>finally</> getting warmer. I’m looking forward to hanging out outdoors again.
The Cherry Blossom Festival here is out of this world.//<portrait=happy>What’s better than getting together and eating good food?
<NPCName>Charles</> was sneezing all night when I saw him at the tavern. Poor guy.
It’s not too uncomfortably hot in the workshop right now. Kind of nice and toasty, actually.
There’s always so much life in Spring. It makes me feel even more alive.
I just love Summer.//<portrait=blushing>Everyone is out and about, and we all have a lot of fun.//I also feel like Summer clothes suit me better. What do you think?
I was reminded yesterday how I hate working in front of the furnace in Summer. I bet you never felt heat like the heat of a furnace on a hot Summer day.
How can I work inside when the day is so beautiful?//<portrait=sad>Sometimes being a blacksmith sucks.
I’m not exaggerating when I say the Beach Cleanup Festival is my favorite. I love seeing the islanders come together and achieve something.
The trash collecting isn’t a contest per se, but…//<portrait=blushing>I like to think that it is.
I don’t know why my little brother keeps shutting himself in.//Doesn’t he realize Summer is the best time to be outside?
I’m so glad it’s starting to cool down. It makes working at the shop much more bearable.
I can’t wait for the Harvest Festival. I wonder what everyone is going to show.
Now that Fall is here, that farm must be working you hard, huh? The season of harvest and all…//I can tell. Farming looks good on you.
Our family has been helping out Starlet Town by setting up festivals and putting up seasonal decorations.//Fall festival decorations are up there on my list of favorites.
I might visit the hot spring one of these days… Clear some leaves for <NPCName>Takeba</>.
It’s starting to get too cold for my taste. I’m not looking forward to Winter…// The hot spring sounds like heaven, huh?
Winter is such a bummer.//I can’t stand being outdoors in the cold too long.
You know what? Sometimes Winter isn’t so bad. At the very least, it makes working in front of the furnace so much better.//<portrait=sad>I’d still rather be outside, though…
On one hand, I get so bored cooped up inside. On the other hand, it’s so dang cold out!//<portrait=sad>What should I do?
Might ask my little brother to go to the hot spring with me next week.//I don’t like him being all alone <Italic>all</> the time.
The furnace can keep the whole house warm, all right…//We don’t need an additional heater.
My little brother and I used to play in the snow until late… When we were kids, of course.//We’d make sleighs from tree trunks and just go sliding back and forth.
So what do you think of the Winter decorations, <PlayerName>$player</>? <NPCName>Rafael</> and I put them up every year.//They’re great, right? Makes the town more festive.
It doesn’t really feel like Winter until I see the festive Winter decorations.
I’m so done with Winter. I need it to be Spring already.
The drilling company?//<portrait=angry>Yeah… Everyone’s talking about it.
How was your first festival? I hope you finally got to meet everyone.
School’s important. I’m glad we get to keep the school going on such a small island.
Talked to <NpcName>Randy</> about it, and he told me it isn’t easy to keep the education budget flowing.

I’m trying to persuade my cousins to expand the inn’s business…//Maybe they could add karaoke! Let people choose songs and sing along.//<portrait=sad>They keep turning me down.//Didn’t see the potential, I guess.

My cousins? Well, the twins who own the inn are <Italic>technically</> my ex cousins-in-law... but we just call them our cousins at this point.//I thought it's pretty normal but maybe it's just my family...
Any big plans for the Summer?
I’ll probably just spend my free time at the Tavern and working on my speakers, as usual.
Ugh, today’s a busy day for me. I could use a cold drink right about now.
<NPCName>Rafael</> and I went over to the inn and had a quick dinner with our niece, <NPCName>Valentina</>, to celebrate her birthday last week.
I gave her a geode because I thought she would enjoy finding treasures, but I guess not…
The annual beach cleanup will take place near the inn, at the beach, and I’m sure everyone will be there to help out.
Any reason is a good reason to get together, eh <PlayerName>$player</>?
Fall is here, and I haven’t gotten anything for <NPCName>Rafael</>’s birthday yet…

<NPCName>Rafael</> loves onyx. I sure hope <NPCName>Ben</> has some in stock right now, or else I don't know what to do.//<portrait=concerned>Do you know where I can get some onyx? Just in case <NPCName>Ben</> doesn't have any.
<NPCName>Rafael</> loves onyx. <NPCName>Ben</> is usually my go-to guy for rare items, but he’s out of town. That’s just great… Do you know where I can get some onyx?
For<NPCName>Rafael</>’s birthday last week, I gave him some cake from the Tavern. He seemed to like it.
I’m going to remind myself, next Summer, to set aside one piece of onyx for his birthday. Because I know <NPCName>Rafael</> loves that stuff.

The last day of Fall is the busiest day for us.//That’s when <NPCName>Rafael</> and I put up Winter decorations around town. You know, so it looks more festive! Adds a little more color than plain white snow.
Have you gotten the greenhouse fixed? You can plant a bunch of different stuff in there, all year round.
The one at your farm is massive, so I’m sure you could plant some trees inside it too.
Are you planting anything in your greenhouse this Winter?
I’m sure you already know this, but plants don’t wither inside the greenhouse. Easy income all year round, eh?
I’m sure you already know this, but plants don’t wither inside the greenhouse. Easy income all year round, eh?
I’m cold. Why does it have to be this cold?!
*shivers*
<NPCName>Ben</> has a friend who mines for a living. Sometimes I ask <NPCName>Ben</> to get some rare ores from her, like zirconium. You know, in exchange for gold plates or weapons.
It can get pretty boring, being indoors all day.
It’s cold, I suppose… Fewer people are out and about.
I see my niece and cousins whenever I can.//<NPCName>Rafael</> and I have a running bet about who’s the better uncle to <NPCName>Valentina</>.//<portrait=normal>Who do you think is winning?
Anyway, those girls are always up to some mischief.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha! I’d hate to miss any of it.
Having a big family means never having to be alone.//But it also means never having enough milk in the fridge!
I might skip Fishensips tonight and just watch some TV at home.
I don’t know… Just don’t feel like it.//<portrait=concerned>Wanna join?
Does it feel like it rains more in the Summer, or is it just me?
It’s raining hard outside, so I might as well keep the furnace on and get some work done.
You here for business or just seeking shelter, <PlayerName>$player</>?
It can be pretty boring being inside all day…//But work is work.
<NPCName>Rafael</> and I used to play in the mud, in weather like this.//<portrait=happy>We would get in so much trouble as soon as Mom found out.//Ha! Good times.
I might go to the tavern after work and play some pool.//<portrait=happy>I hope to see you there!
It’s good to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>!
It’s storming really hard outside, so I might as well keep the furnace on and get some work done.
Are you looking for shelter or here on business, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I can’t believe it’s still storming.//<portrait=concerned>I think I’ll go home soon.
Well, I guess it is Winter.//<portrait=concerned>What else did I expect, besides getting snowed on?
<NPCName>Ben</> has a friend who mines for a living. Sometimes I commission her to get some rare ores, like zirconium…//You know, in exchange for some gold plates.
Oh, do you know her too?//<portrait=concerned>No, I don’t think that’s her. Never mind then.
Ouch! Watch your step!
All good…//<portrait=normal>Thankfully it’s really cold. My toes are probably numb anyway.
<PlayerName>$player</>, you’re covered in snow!//<portrait=annoyed>Eh, what did I expect? It’s Winter.
Still, you should probably stay put for a bit, warm up some.
Well, I guess it is Winter. What else did I expect, besides getting snowed on?
<NPCName>Ben</> has a friend who mines for a living.//Sometimes I commission her to get some rare ores, like zirconium… You know, in exchange for some gold plates.
Oh, do you know her too?
No, I don’t think that’s her. Never mind then.
Ouch! Watch your step!
All good… Thankfully it’s really cold.//My toes are probably numb anyway. Ha ha.
Ouch! Watch your step!
All good.//I don’t blame you. It’s hard to see in this weather.
Long day today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
My arms are tired from working all day, but never too tired for a good game of pool!
My left eye feels funny.//<portrait=annoyed>I think I got dust in it on my way here…
Why is it always in my left eye?//<portrait=happy>I guess it’s time for a new eye. Ha!
Today, I told myself that I would just play a game of pool then go home, but I always manage to talk myself into staying longer.
<NPCName>Rafael</> is very crafty. He knows more about making good weapons than I do.//He has talents.
He’s usually the one who does the final fold of the weapon as well.
Oh, I don’t need a proper heater.//I work in front of the furnace all day.
It must take a lot of planning to run a farm.//What to plant, and when, and so on…
Ha, it's nice to see you there farmer. What are you up to?//Me? Just getting out for some fresh air.
It’s probably not the healthiest habit, staying indoors all day.//<portrait=normal>What brought you here?

This is a popular spot, eh?//<portrait=annoyed>I always see <NPCName>Anne</>
 and <NPCName>Paul</> around here.
It’s true. Their house is right over there.
What brought you to this side of the forest today, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>?
I'm just getting out for some fresh air...and some ores.
It’s probably not the healthiest habit, staying indoors all day.
*busily working on his speaker*
Oh hey! Wanna listen to something?
*plays rock music*
All right. That’s cool!
Oh! Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>, hello!//What brings you here?
Me? I like to help keep it clean.//Folks ought to respect the dead, you know?//It clears my head, too!
Smell that?//Sweet Spring air! I’m so glad Winter is over, ha ha.
The temperature outside only feels right to me in Summer.//Maybe because I’m always in front of a furnace?
Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>, theoretical question! What’s your dream date look like?
Eh, not my thing. I don’t see the appeal of beaches, really.

Special.SourceString: A romantic walk on the beach

Text.SourceString: That sounds perfect! You’ve got the right idea.

Special.SourceString: A delicious home-cooked meal by candlelight

Text.SourceString: Hey, not too shabby! I could go for that. Theoretically. Ha ha!

Special.SourceString: A hiking trip to sleep under the stars

Text.SourceString: That sounds perfect! You’ve got the right idea.

Special.SourceString: A night at the bar with dancing and drinks

Text.SourceString: So, <PlayerName>$player</>! What kind of music do you play to unwind, eh?
Makes sense! That stuff makes me sleepy.
Aw, yeah! Same here!//<portrait=blushing><NPCName>Rafael</> thinks it’s too much, but it helps me let loose.
So refined! Ha ha.
Huh! I like both, really.//<portrait=normal>Got any recommendations?
Read anything interesting lately, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Tell me all about it… I like hearing you talk about the books you read.
Sometimes I come here to get away, but a guy like me rarely minds company.//<portrait=happy>Come on in!
If anything weird ever happens on the farm, come tell me!//I love a good story.
Have you read up on any of the local folklore?//Good stuff, whether you believe it or not.
Me? I guess I’ve never thought about it.//<portrait=normal>I see no reason why those things couldn’t be true.
